flowRoot.flowPara: If the network is identified as being metered, background data is automatically switched off. A notification informs the user.
An icon in the top bar indicates when background data has been disabled.
Background Data switch is presented as a global switch, but it behaves as a network connection configuration option.
When the current network is detected as being metered, background data is disabled, and the switch is insensitive.
When the current network is not detected as being metered, the user can manually toggle background data.
Disabling background data is only recommended for restricted network connections, or connections that are charged according to usage.
When background data is manually disabled for the first time, a message dialog explains when it should be used.
An icon in the top bar indicates when background data has been disabled.
If background data has been manually disabled, it is possible to re-enable it from the system status menu.
